(ABSTRACT) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(This RFC defines the Wilderness - the interstitial space between realms) show newline
(in Cyberspace. It establishes the cosmology of realms, wormholes, and) show newline
(affiliation.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(1. THE WILDERNESS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The Wilderness is the space between all realms. It is not empty - it is) show newline
(the medium through which all connections pass.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    +-----------------------------------------------------------------+) show newline
(    |                                                                 |) show newline
(    |                      THE WILDERNESS                             |) show newline
(    |                                                                 |) show newline
(    |      +---------+              +---------+                      |) show newline
(    |      | Realm A |--wormhole--->| Realm B |                      |) show newline
(    |      +---------+              +---------+                      |) show newline
(    |                                                                 |) show newline
(    |                    +---------+                                  |) show newline
(    |                    | Realm C |                                  |) show newline
(    |                    +---------+                                  |) show newline
(    |                         ^                                       |) show newline
(    |                    \(you are here\)                               |) show newline
(    |                    \(unaffiliated\)                               |) show newline
(    |                                                                 |) show newline
(    +-----------------------------------------------------------------+) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(2. STATES OF BEING) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(2.1 Unaffiliated) show newline
(----------------) show newline
() show newline
(When you first enter Cyberspace, you are unaffiliated. You exist in the) show newline
(Wilderness with no realm to call home.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    You are unaffiliated, in the wilderness.) show newline
() show newline
(This is the starting state. You have not: - Instantiated your own realm) show newline
(- Joined a confederation - Established any identity) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(2.2 Realm Instantiation) show newline
(-----------------------) show newline
() show newline
(To leave the Wilderness, you must instantiate a realm:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    \(create-realm 'myname\)    ; create your own realm) show newline
(    ;; or) show newline
(    \(enroll-request 'myname\)  ; join an existing confederation) show newline
() show newline
(Once affiliated, you have a home:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    You entered the yoyodyne realm 5 minutes ago.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(2.3 Wormhole Transit) show newline
(--------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Wormholes punch through the Wilderness to connect realms. When) show newline
(traversing a wormhole, you pass through the Wilderness - the same) show newline
(Wilderness where the unaffiliated wait.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    realm A --> [wilderness] --> realm B) show newline
(                     ^) show newline
(                wormhole transit) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(3. PROPERTIES OF THE WILDERNESS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(3.1 Universality) show newline
(----------------) show newline
() show newline
(There is one Wilderness. All realms exist as islands within it. All) show newline
(wormholes traverse it.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(3.2 Neutrality) show newline
(--------------) show newline
() show newline
(The Wilderness belongs to no one. It has no authority, no governance, no) show newline
(federation. It simply is.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(3.3 Connectivity) show newline
(----------------) show newline
() show newline
(The Wilderness enables connection. Without it, realms would be isolated.) show newline
(Wormholes work because they have something to traverse.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(4. THE WILDERNESS OF MIRRORS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(A double-entendre:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(4.1 Angleton's Wilderness) show newline
(-------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(James Jesus Angleton, CIA counterintelligence chief, borrowed) show newline
("wilderness of mirrors" from T.S. Eliot to describe the world of) show newline
(espionage. A place where:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Reflexive control is dominant) show newline
(  * Nothing is as it seems) show newline
(  * Disinformation is the norm) show newline
(  * Trust is a vulnerability) show newline
() show newline
(In Cyberspace, the Wilderness acknowledges this reality:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Trust is not given, it is established cryptographically) show newline
(  * Identity is not assumed, it is proven with keys) show newline
(  * Every claim requires verification) show newline
(  * The default stance is skepticism) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(4.2 The Tribal Wilderness) show newline
(-------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The older meaning: outside civilization, unaffiliated with any tribe.) show newline
() show newline
(  * No confederation claims you) show newline
(  * No federation protects you) show newline
(  * You belong to no one) show newline
(  * You are alone) show newline
() show newline
(Both meanings apply. The unaffiliated user is: - In a world where trust) show newline
(must be earned \(Angleton\) - Outside any group until they join one) show newline
(\(tribal\)) show newline
() show newline
(The Wilderness is honest about both. You are alone. Trust nothing but) show newline
(your own crypto keys.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
